## Task

Add idle-triggered memory sync nudge logic to the persistent agent heartbeat loop in `packages/local-agent/src/executor.ts`.

### Background

The heartbeat loop (around line 2055) already:
- Calls `capturePane()` every `HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS` to detect activity via output hash
- Sets `persistentAgent.lastActivityAt = Date.now()` when the hash changes
- Tracks `persistentAgent.lastOutputHash` for change detection

### What to build

#### 1. Add fields to `ActivePersistentAgent` interface (around line 512)

Add two fields:
```typescript
/** Timestamp of last memory sync nudge, or null if not yet nudged this idle period. */
lastMemorySyncAt: number | null;
/** Whether agent was active since last memory sync (used to reset sync state). */
wasActiveAfterSync: boolean;
```

#### 2. Initialise the new fields

In `handlePersistentJob()` where `persistentAgent` is constructed (around line 2033):
```typescript
lastMemorySyncAt: null,
wasActiveAfterSync: false,
```

#### 3. In the heartbeat callback (around line 2064), after the pane hash check:

```typescript
const IDLE_SYNC_THRESHOLD_MS = 5 * 60_000;

if (changed) {
  // Agent became active — reset sync state so next idle period gets a fresh nudge
  persistentAgent.lastMemorySyncAt = null;
  persistentAgent.wasActiveAfterSync = true;
}

const idleSinceActivity = Date.now() - persistentAgent.lastActivityAt;
const shouldNudge =
  idleSinceActivity >= IDLE_SYNC_THRESHOLD_MS &&
  persistentAgent.lastMemorySyncAt === null &&
  !persistentAgent.resetInProgress;

if (shouldNudge) {
  persistentAgent.lastMemorySyncAt = Date.now();
  const syncPrompt =
    "Review this session. If anything worth remembering happened — decisions, preferences, corrections, context — update your .memory/ files. Remove or update any stale memories. If nothing notable, do nothing.";
  try {
    await execFileAsync("tmux", [
      "send-keys",
      "-t",
      persistentAgent.tmuxSession,
      syncPrompt,
      "Enter",
    ]);
    console.log(`[executor] Injected memory sync nudge for ${persistentAgent.role} (idle=${Math.floor(idleSinceActivity / 1000)}s)`);
  } catch (err) {
    console.warn(`[executor] Memory sync nudge failed for ${persistentAgent.role}: ${String(err)}`);
  }
}
```

### Key constraints
- The nudge must only fire ONCE per idle period (guarded by `lastMemorySyncAt === null`)
- Reset `lastMemorySyncAt` to null when `changed === true` (agent became active)
- Must not fire when `resetInProgress` is true
- The nudge text is injected verbatim via `tmux send-keys ... Enter` (same pattern used for message injection elsewhere in the file)
- The constant `IDLE_SYNC_THRESHOLD_MS` can be file-scoped (not exported)

### Files
- `packages/local-agent/src/executor.ts`

### What NOT to do
- Do not use `enqueueMessage()` — send-keys is direct and appropriate for a background nudge
- Do not block or await the nudge in a way that interrupts the heartbeat loop
- Do not add the nudge to ephemeral job polling — persistent agents only
